alc(100vw - 30px)\"/\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/ACra6ez5gWARD3WZMCHAzX.jpg\" alt=\"patio with brick edging\" srcset=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/ACra6ez5gWARD3WZMCHAzX-1920-80.jpg 1920w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/ACra6ez5gWARD3WZMCHAzX-1600-80.jpg 1600w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/ACra6ez5gWARD3WZMCHAzX-1280-80.jpg 1280w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/ACra6ez5gWARD3WZMCHAzX-1024-80.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/ACra6ez5gWARD3WZMCHAzX-768-80.jpg 768w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/ACra6ez5gWARD3WZMCHAzX-415-80.jpg 415w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/ACra6ez5gWARD3WZMCHAzX-360-80.jpg 360w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/ACra6ez5gWARD3WZMCHAzX-320-80.jpg 320w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 710px) 670px, calc(100vw - 30px)\" loading=\"lazy\" data-original-mos=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/ACra6ez5gWARD3WZMCHAzX.jpg\" data-pin-media=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/ACra6ez5gWARD3WZMCHAzX.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\u003cp\u003eWeeds are dislodged in seconds\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003cp\u003e(Image credit: Future / Lisa Fazzani)\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eClearing the entire patio of weeds was a super-speedy job - unlike the time-consuming and back-breaking task that it usually is - and it’s weirdly satisfying seeing everything cleared out of the gaps in just seconds.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe wheel makes it easy to guide the weed sweeper along, plus there is a plastic shield guarding the brush head that prevents any debris from flying upwards. I found it easiest to work row-by-row when it came to my slab paving, going horizontally first, then vertically to cover all areas.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigure data-bordeaux-image-check=\"\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/HwDt6jLB7ZScvaoMP33ryX-1920-80.jpg.webp 1920w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/HwDt6jLB7ZScvaoMP33ryX-1600-80.jpg.webp 1600w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/HwDt6jLB7ZScvaoMP33ryX-1280-80.jpg.webp 1280w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/HwDt6jLB7ZScvaoMP33ryX-1024-80.jpg.webp 1024w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/HwDt6jLB7ZScvaoMP33ryX-768-80.jpg.webp 768w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/HwDt6jLB7ZScvaoMP33ryX-415-80.jpg.webp 415w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/HwDt6jLB7ZScvaoMP33ryX-360-80.jpg.webp 360w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/HwDt6jLB7ZScvaoMP33ryX-320-80.jpg.webp 320w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 710px) 670px, calc(100vw - 30px)\"/\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/HwDt6jLB7ZScvaoMP33ryX.jpg\" alt=\"Weed Sweeper tool with paving slabs\" srcset=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/HwDt6jLB7ZScvaoMP33ryX-1920-80.jpg 1920w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/HwDt6jLB7ZScvaoMP33ryX-1600-80.jpg 1600w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/HwDt6jLB7ZScvaoMP33ryX-1280-80.jpg 1280w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/HwDt6jLB7ZScvaoMP33ryX-1024-80.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/HwDt6jLB7ZScvaoMP33ryX-768-80.jpg 768w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/HwDt6jLB7ZScvaoMP33ryX-415-80.jpg 415w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/HwDt6jLB7ZScvaoMP33ryX-360-80.jpg 360w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/HwDt6jLB7ZScvaoMP33ryX-320-80.jpg 320w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 710px) 670px, calc(100vw - 30px)\" loading=\"lazy\" data-original-mos=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/HwDt6jLB7ZScvaoMP33ryX.jpg\" data-pin-media=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/HwDt6jLB7ZScvaoMP33ryX.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe plastic shield prevents debris flying upwards\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003cp\u003e(Image credit: Future / Lisa Fazzani)\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eI was also impressed by the extra-long 10m cable, meaning that I could plug it straight in without the need for an outdoor extension cable (as with my lawn mower). The safety button feature is another bonus.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eI found the nylon brush head worked well on my patio paving, but swapped over to the tougher wire brush when I moved onto the front garden path and pavement. The concrete slabs weren’t a problem at all for it, with the weeds cleared from the path in seconds again.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigure data-bordeaux-image-check=\"\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/vPjn3hPgkkeDRKGSHPwwyX-1920-80.jpg.webp 1920w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/vPjn3hPgkkeDRKGSHPwwyX-1600-80.jpg.webp 1600w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/vPjn3hPgkkeDRKGSHPwwyX-1280-80.jpg.webp 1280w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/vPjn3hPgkkeDRKGSHPwwyX-1024-80.jpg.webp 1024w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/vPjn3hPgkkeDRKGSHPwwyX-768-80.jpg.webp 768w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/vPjn3hPgkkeDRKGSHPwwyX-415-80.jpg.webp 415w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/vPjn3hPgkkeDRKGSHPwwyX-360-80.jpg.webp 360w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/vPjn3hPgkkeDRKGSHPwwyX-320-80.jpg.webp 320w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 710px) 670px, calc(100vw - 30px)\"/\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/vPjn3hPgkkeDRKGSHPwwyX.jpg\" alt=\"Weed Sweeper tool on pavement\" srcset=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/vPjn3hPgkkeDRKGSHPwwyX-1920-80.jpg 1920w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/vPjn3hPgkkeDRKGSHPwwyX-1600-80.jpg 1600w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/vPjn3hPgkkeDRKGSHPwwyX-1280-80.jpg 1280w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/vPjn3hPgkkeDRKGSHPwwyX-1024-80.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/vPjn3hPgkkeDRKGSHPwwyX-768-80.jpg 768w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/vPjn3hPgkkeDRKGSHPwwyX-415-80.jpg 415w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/vPjn3hPgkkeDRKGSHPwwyX-360-80.jpg 360w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/vPjn3hPgkkeDRKGSHPwwyX-320-80.jpg 320w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 710px) 670px, calc(100vw - 30px)\" loa